    "department": "Customer Operations",
    "description": "WHY CLIPBOARD EXISTS:\n\nWe exist to lift as many people up the socioeconomic ladder as possible. We dramatically improve lives by letting professionals turn extra time and ambition into career growth and financial opportunity. We achieve this with our app-based marketplace that connects workplaces and professionals, allowing professionals to book on-demand shifts and workplaces to access on-demand talent.\n\n\nABOUT CLIPBOARD:\n\nClipboard is a fast-growing Series C marketplace. We are a leader in our Long Term Care vertical and are expanding into several others (Dental, Home Health, etc.), as well as building out a full-time product.\nWe are a YC Top Company https://www.ycombinator.com/topcompanies/ with a global, remote team of 1,000+ people. We have been profitable since 2022, and fill millions of shifts annually at partner workplaces across the U.S., where tens of thousands of professionals work with us every year.\nWe are looking for your help to keep growing so we can serve more professionals and workplaces.\n\nTo learn more about us, take a look at our website here https://www.clipboardhealth.com/careers.\n\nAbout the Role\nWe’re looking for a Knowledge Management Specialist to design, maintain, and continuously improve the frameworks that power our internal healthcare operations. You’ll own the accuracy, structure, and usability of our internal knowledge ecosystem — ensuring that every process, workflow, and SOP helps teams make faster, better-informed decisions.\n\nThis role sits at the intersection of operations, documentation, and systems design. You’ll dive deep into how things work, identify where clarity breaks down, and turn complex workflows into precise, usable knowledge. It’s a highly visible individual contributor role with significant operational impact — not a managerial position, but one where your work influences how entire teams function.\n\n\nWHAT YOU’LL DO\n\n - Analyze and structure complex healthcare workflows into accurate, easy-to-follow SOPs and internal documentation.\n\n - Audit and refine our knowledge base to eliminate redundancies, close content gaps, and improve accessibility.\n\n - Act as the internal knowledge point of contact, identifying recurring questions or knowledge gaps and proactively resolving them through documentation updates or process improvements.\n\n - Partner with operations and compliance teams to ensure documentation accuracy and alignment with real-world processes.\n\n - Continuously improve how our teams access and use internal knowledge, proposing structural or systemic enhancements.\n\n\nWHAT YOU’LL BRING\n\n - 3+ years of experience in knowledge management, process documentation, or operational enablement — ideally in healthcare, tech, or other regulated industries.\n\n - Proven ability to turn complex, technical processes into clear, actionable documentation.\n\n - Strong systems-thinking mindset and an analytical approach to process design.\n\n - Hands-on experience with tools like Confluence, Notion, Zendesk, and Google Workspace.\n\n - Detail-oriented and self-driven, with the ability to manage multiple documentation and improvement projects simultaneously.\n\nSystem Requirements\n\n - Stable wired internet connection (15+ Mbps)\n\n - Modern computer meeting or exceeding: i5 8th Gen or Ryzen 5 2000 series, 12GB RAM minimum (16GB preferred)\n\n - Noise-canceling headset, quiet workspace, and power backup\n\n\nWHY THIS ROLE MATTERS\n\nYour work ensures that every operational decision across the organization rests on a solid foundation of accurate, accessible knowledge. As one of the first hires dedicated purely to knowledge systems and process clarity, you’ll play a key role in shaping how our teams learn, execute, and scale.\n\n\nWHAT SUCCESS LOOKS LIKE\n\n - Teams can find precise, up-to-date information with minimal friction.\n\n - SOPs are clear, consistent, and aligned with real-world execution.\n\n - You become the go-to person for clarity and structure in operational documentation.\n\n\nHIRING PROCESS\n\nYou’ll complete a short practical exercise designed to assess how you structure and communicate complex information clearly and logically.\n\nQuick Note on Scammers:\n\nClipboard would never ask you for money or your bank details to participate in our hiring process. Report any scammers impersonating the Clipboard hiring team members here https://forms.gle/SyGaxHFbon7Hg9fW6.",
